@function_pdx Mural • Completed April 2023 35’x7’ • All Aerosol

The Function Bar in NW Portland off of 23rd street, is a unique and beautiful watering hole. They are a beer tap takeover and event rental space that also has a gorgeous covered outdoor lounge, more like an outdoor living room that can be enjoyed all seasons. We collaboratively settled on a design that promoted the environmental vibe of this outdoor room and expanded upon the existing plants on the patio. Our goal was to create a “living wall”, immersive, natural and a subtle experience. This was a very challenging mural, totally new territory for me. It required over 40 colors of greens, blue, turquoise and other misfit tertiary colors so that all the tropical plants each had an individual hue. Otherwise it would have appeared as a tantamount monochromatic two dimensional mess. The lady bug is just barely 10”.

